-- Week 1
mon
  Overview of assessment.
  Introduction to formalization and to Lean.
tue
  Difference between <code>Bool</code> and <code>Prop</code>, basic tactics: <code>exact?</code>,  <code>apply</code>, <code>constructor</code>, <code>cases</code>.
_tentative

-- Week 2
mon
  Syntax, infoview, <code>rfl</code>, <code>inductive</code>s, preliminary discussion about project topics.
tue
  Tactics, structuring proofs (<a href="https://github.com/adomani/MA4N1_Theorem_proving_with_Lean/blob/master/MA4N1/L00_intro.lean">L00_intro.lean</a>)
sup
  Functional programming, object oriented programming, more proofs.

-- Week 3
mon
  Begin with <a href="https://github.com/adomani/MA4N1_Theorem_proving_with_Lean/blob/master/MA4N1/L01_polynomials.lean">polynomials</a>.
tue
  Coordinate projects.
  Start assigning groups.
sup
  Implicit vs explicit variables.
  Dependent Cartesian Product <code>< , ></code>.
  Addition of two even numbers is even.
  Negation.
  Contradiction (absurd).

